  "prompt": "I told him I liked him and he didn't give me an actual answer! Help?",
  "response": "It can be really confusing and frustrating when someone doesn't give a clear response to your feelings. Here are a few steps you can take to clarify the situation:\n\n1. **Give It Some Time**: He may need some time to process what you said and figure out his feelings. Sometimes people don\u2019t know how to respond initially.\n\n2. **Initiate a Conversation**: When you feel ready, have an honest conversation with him. You could say something like, \"When I told you I liked you, I felt like I didn\u2019t get a clear response. Could we talk about it more?\"\n\n3. **Be Direct**: Make sure you clearly express your feelings and ask for clarity about his. Being direct can help avoid misunderstandings.\n\n4. **Observe His Behavior**: Sometimes actions speak louder than words. Pay attention to how he behaves around you after your confession.\n\n5. **Prepare for Any Outcome**: Be ready for any response he may give. He might need more time, he might not have the same feelings, or he might reciprocate but be unsure how to express it.\n\nRemember, getting clarity is important for both of you. No matter how difficult it might seem, having an open and honest dialogue can help you both move forward.",
